The only Oscar for Citizen Kane was for the script. The Directors Guild nevertheless named him best director that year. The latest casualties are directors James L.  Brooks, whose movie Broadcast News was nominated though he wasn't, and Spielberg who was left out in the cold with his Empire of the Sun. They have never won Academy Awards for their individual achievements. The honorary award has also proved useful to salve the Academy's conscience. Such flagrant omissions are often cited by critics as evidence of the unfairness of Hollywood's highest prize. For example, Citizen Kane, which customarily places No. 